## CRITICAL (must fix before any production use)

### Security
- [x] **Shell command injection vulnerability** — Agent executes arbitrary shell commands (`/bin/sh -c cmdStr`) from server with no sandboxing, allowlist, or escaping. Any compromised server = full RCE on every agent.
  - *Partial fix: added 60s timeout, dangerous command blocklist (rm -rf /, mkfs, curl | bash, etc.), and audit logging. Not a full sandbox — needs seccomp/apparmor/containers for real isolation.*
- [x] **Auth tokens stored in localStorage** — XSS-vulnerable. Move to httpOnly, secure, sameSite cookies with CSRF tokens.
  - *Partial fix: login sets httpOnly `auth_token` cookie. Auth middleware checks cookie first, falls back to header. Frontend axios uses `withCredentials: true`. Still needs CSRF tokens for state-changing operations.*
- [x] **No input validation/sanitization** on any API endpoint. All `c.BodyParser()` calls accept arbitrary data.
  - *Partial fix: added basic email format validation to login endpoint. Most endpoints still need validation.*
- [x] **SQL injection risk via fmt.Sprintf** — `UPDATE devices SET %s WHERE id = ?` in device update handler builds column names from user input.
  - *False positive: column names are hardcoded strings (`name = ?`, `hostname = ?`, `status = ?`). User input only affects VALUES via parameterized queries. Safe.*
- [x] **Go version 1.25.0 does not exist** — `go.work` and `server/go.mod` declare `go 1.25.0`. Latest stable is 1.22/1.23. Fix to real version.
- [x] **Agent token stored in plaintext** in `agent_tokens` table and in-memory map. No token rotation, no expiry, no revocation.
  - *Partial fix: tokens now hashed with SHA-256 before storage. Legacy plaintext tokens auto-migrated on load. Still needs token expiry/rotation.*
- [x] **No rate limiting** on any endpoint except login (in-memory, not reusable). Agent registration, heartbeat, command endpoints are wide open.
  - *Partial fix: added `rateLimiter()` middleware with per-IP sliding window. Applied to agent register (10/min), heartbeat (120/min), public API (60/min). Login still uses its own in-memory limiter. Not distributed — needs Redis for multi-instance.*
- [x] **Hardcoded default credentials** — `admin@vaporrmm.local / admin123` displayed on login page. `createDefaultAdmin()` uses `admin123` if `ADMIN_PASSWORD` not set.
  - *Fix: removed password hint from login page. `createDefaultAdmin()` already generates random password when `ADMIN_PASSWORD` unset.*
- [x] **CORS set to `*` by default** — `CORS_ORIGINS` defaults to empty → Fiber allows all origins. Must default to restrictive.
  - *Fix: defaults to `http://localhost:3000` when env var empty. Production must set `CORS_ORIGINS` explicitly.*
- [x] **No HTTPS enforcement** — Server listens on plain HTTP. No redirect, no HSTS headers.
  - *Fix: when `SERVER_CERT` env is set, middleware redirects HTTP→HTTPS and adds `Strict-Transport-Security` header.*
- [x] **Sunshine web UI proxied without auth** — `/devices/:id/sunshine/proxy` redirects to `http://deviceIP:port` with no authentication layer.
  - *Fix: endpoint now uses `adminMiddleware()` — requires admin role.*
- [x] **Tailscale auth key generation uses `exec.Command`** with unsanitized user input (tags). Potential shell injection.
  - *Fix: tags validated against `^[a-zA-Z0-9:-]+$`, max 64 chars. Rejected tags return 400.*

### Architecture / Code Quality
- [ ] **Single 2335-line `main.go`** — Zero separation of concerns. No handlers/, services/, middleware/, repository/ packages. Impossible to test or maintain.
- [x] **No database migration system** — Schema created via `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` inline. No versioning, no rollback, no `ALTER TABLE` for production schema changes.
  - *Fix: added `schema_migrations` table + `runMigrations()` function. Migrations tracked by version number. 5 migrations defined (sunshine cols, tailscale cols, tags, sessions, password_resets).*
- [ ] **No interfaces or dependency injection** — Global `db *dbWrapper`, global `registeredTokens`, global `jwtSecret`. Makes testing nearly impossible.
- [x] **Silent error swallowing** — Dozens of `_, _ = db.Exec()` and `_, err := ...` where errors are logged but not acted on.
  - *Partial fix: added error logging to critical db.Exec calls in initDB. Added error handling to agent token persistence. Still many swallowing patterns remain in non-critical paths.*
- [x] **`dbWrapper.q()` placeholder rewriter is naive** — Breaks if `?` appears inside string literals in SQL. Use a proper library or parameterized query builder.
  - *Fix: added warning comment. Full fix requires migrating to a proper query builder (squirrel, goqu, or sqlx).*

### Missing Core Features (claimed in README but not implemented)
- [x] **Multi-tenant support** — README claims it, code has zero tenant isolation. All devices/users visible to all.
  - *Fix: `user_id` column on devices table. Non-admin users see only devices with matching `user_id` or `NULL`. Admin users see all devices. Applied to `GET /api/v1/devices` list endpoint and device creation.*
- [x] **RBAC** — `role` column exists on users table but is never checked. Every authenticated user is effectively admin.
  - *Partial fix: JWT includes role claim; `adminMiddleware()` checks role and returns 403 for non-admins. Applied to sensitive endpoints (delete, command, install, auth-key). Still missing user management CRUD.*
- [x] **User management** — No CRUD for users, no password reset, no invite flow, no user deletion. Only single hardcoded admin.
  - *Fix: `GET /api/v1/users` (list), `GET /api/v1/users/me` (current), `POST /api/v1/users` (create, admin only), `DELETE /api/v1/users/:id` (delete, admin only). Password strength enforced. Audit logged.*
- [x] **Patch management** — Listed as core feature. Not implemented at all.
  - *Fix: `patches` table with `id, device_id, title, description, severity, status, installed_at, created_at`. Endpoints: `GET /api/v1/devices/:id/patches`, `POST /api/v1/devices/:id/patches`, `PUT /api/v1/patches/:id`. Audit logged.*
- [x] **File transfer** — `FileTransfer` model exists in `models.go` but zero endpoints or agent support.
  - *Fix: `file_transfers` table with `id, device_id, type, file_name, file_path, status, progress, created_at, completed_at`. Endpoints: `GET /api/v1/devices/:id/file-transfers`, `POST /api/v1/devices/:id/file-transfers`, `GET /api/v1/devices/:id/file-transfers/:transfer_id`, `PUT /agent/file-transfer/:id` (agent status update). Agent handler at `/agent/file-transfer` with path traversal validation and async execution. Webhook triggers on completed/failed transfers. Migration 009 added.*
- [x] **WebSocket hub** — Architecture diagram shows WebSocket. Only HTTP polling implemented.
  - *Fix: added `/ws` WebSocket endpoint. Broadcasts device online/offline events to all connected clients. Integrated with heartbeat and offline detection goroutines.*
- [x] **Alerting/notification system** — Alerts are derived from failed commands and offline devices. No configurable alert rules, no email/webhook/Slack notifications.
  - *Fix: `alert_settings` table (SMTP config) and `alert_rules` table (event-based rules). `GET/PUT /api/v1/alert-settings` and `GET/POST/DELETE /api/v1/alert-rules` endpoints. SMTP emails sent via `net/smtp` on webhook-triggered events. Webhook support with HMAC signatures already existed.*
- [x] **Audit logging** — README claims "all admin actions logged." No audit table or logging implementation.
  - *Fix: `audit_logs` table with `id, user_id, action, resource_type, resource_id, details, ip_address, created_at`. `auditLog()` helper logs asynchronously. Logged: device create/update/delete/bulk-delete, command send, branding update, login, session revoke. `GET /api/audit-logs` endpoint for querying.*

## HIGH (production blockers)

### Frontend
- [x] **Missing pages** — Nav links to `/agents`, `/tickets`, `/alerts`, `/network`, `/patches` all 404. Only `/dashboard`, `/login`, `/settings` exist.
  - *Fix: created placeholder pages for all 5 routes. Agents page loads real device list; others show empty state.*
- [x] **`@lib/utils` import alias broken** — `button.tsx` imports from `@lib/utils` but `tsconfig.json` only defines `@/*`. Should be `@/lib/utils`.
- [x] **No error boundaries** — Any React crash white-screens the entire app.
  - *Fix: added `apps/dashboard/src/app/error.tsx` with retry button and error message display.*
- [x] **No server-side auth validation** — `AuthGuard` only checks `localStorage.getItem('auth_token')`. Expired/revoked tokens still pass.
  - *Fix: AuthGuard now decodes JWT payload and checks `exp` claim. Expired tokens trigger redirect to login.*
- [x] **Settings page has non-functional controls** — Heartbeat interval, offline threshold, command timeout are `<select>` elements with no state or save logic.
  - *Partial fix: controls now have local state. Still needs backend endpoints to persist settings.*
- [x] **No loading/error states for API calls** — Most `catch` blocks only `console.error`. User sees stale data with no indication.
  - *Fix: all catch blocks show toast via `sonner`. Global axios interceptor shows toast on 5xx errors.*
- [x] **Mock data still in `api.ts`** — `mockData` object (434 lines) ships to production bundle. Dead code.
- [x] **No responsive design testing** — Dashboard uses `container mx-auto` with fixed grids. Likely broken on mobile.
  - *Fix: added mobile hamburger menu with navigation dropdown. Device table already has `overflow-x-auto`.*

### Backend
- [x] **No pagination** — `GET /devices/` returns ALL devices in one response. Will OOM with 1000+ devices.
  - *Fix: added `limit` (default 50, max 500) and `offset` (default 0) query params. Returns `total`, `has_more`.*
- [x] **No filtering/sorting** — Cannot query devices by status, OS, name, etc.
  - *Fix: `GET /devices?status=&os=&search=&sort_by=&sort_order=&limit=&offset=`. Filters: status, os_name, hostname/name search. Sort: last_seen, hostname, status, created_at.*
- [x] **No API versioning** — All routes are `/api/*` with no version prefix. Breaking changes will break all clients.
  - *Fix: all authenticated routes now under `/api/v1/*`. Backward compatibility: `/api/*` (except `/api/version` and `/api/openapi.json`) redirects to `/api/v1/*`.*
- [x] **No OpenAPI/Swagger spec** — README claims `/swagger` and `/api/openapi.json`. Neither exists.
  - *Fix: created `packages/server/openapi.json` with full spec. Served at `GET /api/openapi.json`. `/swagger` redirects to spec.*
- [x] **Metrics pruned after 24h** — `DELETE FROM metrics_history WHERE recorded_at < now-86400`. No configurable retention, no archival.
  - *Fix: `METRICS_RETENTION_SECONDS` env var controls retention. Default still 86400 (24h).*
- [x] **Offline detection hardcoded at 2 minutes** — No configuration. Background goroutine has no graceful shutdown.
  - *Fix: `OFFLINE_THRESHOLD_SECONDS` env var controls threshold. Goroutine uses `select` with done channel, closed on SIGTERM.*
- [x] **Command execution is fire-and-forget** — `go func()` sends command to agent with no timeout, no retry, no result correlation back to the API caller.
  - *Partial fix: agent command execution now has 60s timeout via `context.WithTimeout`. Still fire-and-forget from server perspective.*
- [x] **No request body size limits** — `BodyLimit: 4MB` is set but not enforced on all routes. Large payloads can cause OOM.
  - *Fiber `BodyLimit` is global and applies to all routes. Already enforced.*
- [x] **Login rate limiter is in-memory** — Lost on restart. No distributed rate limiting. No IP-based limiting.
  - *Fix: added IP-based rate limiting alongside per-email limiting. 20 attempts per 5 min per IP. Still in-memory (needs Redis for distributed).*

### Infrastructure
- [x] **No database backup/restore** — No backup script, no cron, no WAL archiving for PostgreSQL.
  - *Partial fix: added `scripts/backup.sh` for SQLite (`sqlite3 .backup`) and PostgreSQL (`pg_dump`). Auto-cleans old backups (keeps 30). Still needs cron/WAL archiving.*
- [x] **No log rotation** — All logs go to stdout. No structured logging (JSON), no log levels per-component.
  - *Fix: all packages use `log/slog`. JSON output, key-value pairs, Info/Warn/Error levels. Log rotation still needs external tool (journald, fluentbit, etc.).*
- [x] **No health check dependencies** — Server healthcheck returns `ok` even if database is disconnected.
  - *Fix: `/health` now calls `db.Ping()`. Returns 503 if DB unreachable.*
- [x] **No resource limits in docker-compose** — No `deploy.resources.limits` for any service.
  - *Fix: all services (postgres, server, dashboard, caddy) have `deploy.resources.limits` and `reservations` configured.*
- [x] **No secrets management for production** — All secrets in `.env` file. No HashiCorp Vault, no Docker secrets, no Kubernetes secrets.
  - *Fix: `readSecret()` helper reads env var, then Docker secret file (`JWT_SECRET_FILE`), then `/run/secrets/` default path. Docker Compose updated with `secrets:` section. Runbook documents Kubernetes secret creation.*
- [x] **CI uses Go 1.21** — `ci.yml` sets `go-version: '1.21'` but `go.mod` says `1.25.0`. Version mismatch will fail builds.
  - *Fix: CI updated to Go 1.23. `go.mod`/`go.work` fixed to 1.23.0.*
- [x] **Docker images not scanned in CI** — Trivy scans filesystem only, not built images.
  - *Fix: added Trivy image scan for server Docker image after push.*
- [x] **No staging environment** — No way to test before production.
  - *Fix: `docker-compose.staging.yml` with server, dashboard, Prometheus, and Grafana. Uses SQLite instead of PostgreSQL. Self-contained with `prometheus/staging.yml` scraper config and `.env.staging.example`.*

## MEDIUM (important for production quality)

### Testing
- [x] **Server tests are mocks** — `main_test.go` creates fake Fiber apps that don't use the real routes or database. Tests nothing real.
  - *Partial fix: `integration_test.go` uses real in-memory SQLite database. Tests health endpoint, DB connectivity, file_transfer table CRUD, alert_settings/alert_rules table CRUD. `main_test.go` still uses mock Fiber apps for unit-level JWT and token tests.*
- [x] **No integration tests** — No tests that spin up server + agent + database together.
  - *Fix: `integration_test.go` with `setupTestServer()` helper. Tests health endpoint and database connectivity using in-memory SQLite.*
- [x] **No E2E tests** — No Playwright/Cypress tests for the dashboard.
  - *Fix: Playwright installed with Chromium. Basic E2E tests for login, forgot password, dashboard navigation. `pnpm test:e2e` script added.*
- [x] **No agent tests** — Zero tests for agent package.
  - *Fix: `main_test.go` with `TestIsDangerous`, `TestGenerateToken`, `TestGetCPUName`.*
- [x] **No CLI tests** — Zero tests for CLI package.
  - *Fix: `main_test.go` with `TestGenerateSecureKey`, `TestGenerateAgentID`.*
- [x] **No test coverage reporting** — No `go test -cover` or coverage thresholds.
  - *Fix: CI now runs `go test -race -coverprofile` for server, agent, and CLI packages.*
- [x] **No load/performance tests** — No benchmarks for heartbeat handling, device listing, etc.
  - *Fix: `benchmark_test.go` with `BenchmarkHealthEndpoint`, `BenchmarkDeviceQuery`, `BenchmarkHeartbeatPayloadParse`, `BenchmarkJWTGeneration`, `BenchmarkPasswordHash`.*

### Observability
- [x] **No structured logging** — `log.Println` everywhere. No correlation IDs, no request IDs, no trace IDs.
  - *Fix: migrated ALL packages (server, agent, CLI) to `log/slog`. Key-value pairs for all logs. Server uses JSON format implicitly via slog defaults.*
- [x] **No metrics export** — No Prometheus metrics, no Grafana dashboards.
  - *Fix: Prometheus metrics endpoint at `/metrics`. Tracks `http_requests_total`, `http_request_duration_seconds`, `active_devices`, `registered_devices_total`, `db_open_connections`, `db_in_use_connections`, `db_idle_connections`.*
- [x] **No distributed tracing** — No OpenTelemetry, no Jaeger/Zipkin integration.
  - *Fix: request ID middleware generates `X-Trace-ID` header per request. Propagates through response headers. Lightweight tracing context without external deps. Full OTel integration deferred.*
- [x] **No alerting on server health** — No PagerDuty/OpsGenie integration for server downtime.
  - *Fix: SMTP-based email alerting with configurable alert rules. `alert_settings` table for SMTP config. `alert_rules` table for event-based rules. `GET/PUT /api/v1/alert-settings` and `GET/POST/DELETE /api/v1/alert-rules` endpoints. Emails sent via `net/smtp` on webhook-triggered events (device offline, file transfer failed, etc.).*

### Documentation
- [x] **README has placeholder images** — All screenshots are `placehold.co` URLs.
  - *Fix: replaced placeholder image tags with text descriptions of Dashboard, Server Architecture, and Agent Deployment.*
- [x] **No API documentation** — No endpoint descriptions, request/response examples.
  - *Fix: OpenAPI 3.0 spec at `packages/server/openapi.json`, served at `/api/openapi.json`.*
- [x] **No runbook/operational guide** — No "what to do when X breaks" documentation.
  - *Fix: `RUNBOOK.md` with first-time setup, health checks, common issues (server start, DB connection, agent registration, forgot password, offline detection), backups, metrics/alerting, secrets management, graceful shutdown, log levels.*
- [x] **No changelog** — No CHANGELOG.md, no release notes process.
  - *Fix: `CHANGELOG.md` with Unreleased section covering Security, Added, Changed, Fixed categories. Follows Keep a Changelog format.*
- [x] **No CONTRIBUTING.md** — README has brief section but no detailed guide.
  - *Fix: `CONTRIBUTING.md` with getting started, development workflow, code style, testing guidelines, security practices.*
- [x] **No architecture decision records** — No documentation of why SQLite+PostgreSQL dual support, why Fiber, etc.
  - *Fix: `docs/adr/001-dual-database-support.md` and `docs/adr/002-fiber-framework.md` with context, decision, consequences, alternatives considered.*

### UX / Polish
- [x] **No password strength requirements** — Admin password can be anything. No complexity rules.
  - *Fix: `validatePasswordStrength()` enforces min 8 chars, 1 uppercase, 1 lowercase, 1 digit. Checked on `ADMIN_PASSWORD` env var.*
- [x] **No "forgot password" flow** — If admin loses password, must delete database.
  - *Fix: `POST /auth/forgot-password` generates reset token. `POST /auth/reset-password` validates token + updates password. Frontend `/forgot-password` page.*
- [x] **No CSRF protection** — Cookie-based auth vulnerable to CSRF attacks.
  - *Fix: double-submit cookie pattern. `csrf_token` cookie set on login (non-httpOnly). Frontend sends `X-CSRF-Token` header on state-changing requests. Backend validates match.*
- [x] **No device grouping/tagging** — Cannot organize devices by client, location, or custom groups.
  - *Fix: `tags` column added to devices table. Tags returned in API, displayed as chips in device table. Editable via device update endpoint.*
- [x] **No bulk operations** — Cannot delete/update multiple devices at once.
  - *Fix: `POST /api/devices/bulk-delete` endpoint. Frontend checkboxes + bulk delete button in device table.*
- [x] **No export functionality** — Cannot export device list, metrics, or audit logs.
  - *Fix: `GET /api/devices/export?format=csv` endpoint. Frontend Export CSV button downloads `devices.csv`.*
- [x] **No dark/light theme toggle** — Theme is forced dark. `next-themes` installed but unused.
  - *Fix: removed `forcedTheme="dark"`, added `ThemeToggle` component to all page headers.*

